.TH Take 1
.SH NAME
take \- easily slice and substring text.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B take
[\fB\-l\fR]
[\fB\-\-by\-lines\fR]
.IR start 
.IR stop
.IR step
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B take 
slices a string using a start index (inclusive), stop index (exclusive) and step size
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP \[bu] 2
echo "Hello" | take 0 -0 1    # returns "Hello
.IP \[bu] 
echo "Hello" | take 0 -0 -1   # returns "olleH"
.IP \[bu]
echo "Hello" | take 1 3 1     # returns "el"
.IP \[bu] 
echo "Hello" | take 0 -1 1    # returns "Hell"
.IP \[bu]
echo "Hello" | take -3 -1 1   # returns "ll"
.IP \[bu]
echo "Hello" | take 0 -0 2    # returns "Hlo"
.IP \[bu]
echo "Hello\nWorld\n" | take -l -1 -0 1 
